---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import addons from "../images/addons.png";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resources - minomino">
  <div class="my-6 mx-6 md:mx-auto md:max-w-4xl" transition:name="card">
    <article class="max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Resources</h2>
      <article
        class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-a:text-primary prose-a:no-underline max-w-4xl"
      >
        <p>
          These resources are largely compiled from other resource pages. I
          compiled the ones that I specifically use/have used to be less large.
        </p>
        <p>
          I may include many different links for one category. The best will be
          labeled with a ✨ and ones that I use will be bolded.
        </p>
        <p>This page is a WIP.</p>
        <h3>Resource Pages</h3>
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors font-bold"
          href="https://learnjapanese.moe/resources/"
          >TheMoeWay Resources Page</a
        > (✨) - Very comprehensive. I've used a lot from here.
        <br />
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors"
          href="https://www.notion.so/Refold-Japanese-Content-Resources-WIP-9121097535e74f6ba501c93b1773e70c"
          >Refold Resources Page</a
        > - Haven't used much. Some content recommendations.
        <h3>Anki</h3>
        <h4>Anki Decks</h4>
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors font-bold"
          href="https://anacreondjt.gitlab.io/docs/coredeck/">Core 2.3k</a
        > (✨) - A popular, free deck. You might've heard people refer to a Core
        2k/6k deck, this is an improved version of that. My top recommendation since
        it's free.
        <br />
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors"
          href="https://refold.la/japanese/deck/">Refold JP1K</a
        > - 1,000 common words used in slice-of-life anime, best if starting with
        anime. The deck is high quality but overpriced.
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors"
          href="https://github.com/donkuri/Kaishi">Kaishi 1.5k</a
        > - A free modern deck to introduce beginners to basic Japanese vocabulary.
        <br />
        <h4>Anki Note Types</h4>
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors font-bold"
          href="https://arbyste.github.io/jp-mining-note-prerelease/"
          >JP Mining Note</a
        > (✨) - This is THE note type. It's packed full of features and is very
        flexible. This is easily my favorite.
        <br />
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors"
          href="https://aquafina-water-bottle.github.io/jp-mining-note/alternatives/#note-types"
          >Aquafina's Alternatives Page</a
        > - Every notable alternative. I'd use Anime Cards if I wasn't using JP Mining
        Note.
        <br />
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors font-bold"
          href="https://github.com/donkuri/Lapis"
          >Lapis</a
        > - An alternative to the no longer maintained JP Mining Note to fix some of its issues.
        <h4>Anki Addons</h4>
        <a
          class="hover:text-mino-500 transition-colors font-bold"
          href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oaRPN88O071bzvUJtdHCInvLF8n9BCln/view?usp=sharing"
          >Anki Addon Pack</a
        > (✨) - These are the Anki addons I have installed. You can unzip this into
        your addons21 folder. Make sure to check for updates after installing.
        <Image src={addons} alt="Anki Addon Pack" class="mx-auto rounded-lg" />
      </article>
    </article>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
